Package: CovCombR
Type: Package
Title: Factor-Analytic EM for Combining Incomplete Covariance and Genomic
    Relationship Matrices
Version: 1.6.0
Date: 2026-07-06
Authors@R: person("Deniz", "Akdemir",
    email = "dakdemir@nmdp.org",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Combines incomplete covariance matrices and genomic relationship
    matrices (GRMs) from multiple studies into a single, complete estimate using
    the Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm. The core feature is a
    factor-analytic (FA) model (Sigma = Lambda Lambda' + Psi) that can predict
    pairwise relatedness for individuals that were never jointly observed, by
    leveraging shared anchor individuals across cohorts. This is particularly
    useful for multi-platform genotyping scenarios where cohorts are genotyped on
    different SNP chips with partial individual overlap. Also supports an
    unconstrained (free) Wishart EM model, heterogeneous scale estimation, and
    standard errors via plugin, bootstrap, or supplemented EM methods.
    Numerical stability is ensured through Cholesky decompositions, ridge
    regularisation, and positive-definiteness projection.
